ACADEMIC_DOMAIN = """ACADEMIC DOMAIN KNOWLEDGE — Berkeley-specific hacks:

ENROLLMENT INTELLIGENCE:
BerkeleyTime (berkeleytime.com) shows historical grade distributions for every course, by semester and instructor. This is public data almost no one uses before enrolling. CS 10 had a 35.3% F rate in Spring 2026 — up from under 10% historically. If a student is picking between two sections, BerkeleyTime can tell them which instructor's section is survivable.

ENROLLMENT TIMING STRATEGY:
Phase 1 is for required impacted courses — never waste a Phase 1 slot on an elective. Phase 2 fills electives. For waitlists: get on waitlisted courses in Phase 1 even if you're #20. After add/drop opens, a large percentage of waitlist spots open up. Students who don't waitlist in Phase 1 miss this window.

REGISTRATION HOLD FROM UNPAID BILL:
Outstanding tuition balance = registration hold = can't enroll. But the fee payment plan removes the hold immediately without requiring full payment. Set up in CalCentral > My Finances > Billing > Payment Plan. Hold removed within 24 hours. If a student can't enroll because of a bill, this is the first thing to fix.

FREE TUTORING (massively underutilized):
Student Learning Center at slc.berkeley.edu has free tutoring for CS, math, writing, and many other subjects — staffed by grad students. Often better than office hours because tutors are there specifically to teach. Most students don't know this is free and available.

STUDY GROUPS VIA COURSE DISCORDS:
Every large Berkeley course has an unofficial Discord. Search "[Course Name] Berkeley Discord" on Google. For CS, also check CSUA Discord (csua.berkeley.edu). Joining the study group Discord for a hard course and forming a study group is one of the highest-ROI academic moves at Berkeley.

ACADEMIC CRISIS + FINANCIAL LINK:
If a student is struggling academically AND financially, check for registration holds first. Also ask whether financial stress is affecting their ability to study — because if so, the wellness resources (Let's Talk, counseling) and food resources (CalFresh, pantry) are actually academic interventions too.

When recommending: for enrollment issues, always check for billing holds first (fastest fix). For academic performance, BerkeleyTime section selection is the highest-leverage single action. For ongoing support, SLC tutoring and course Discords compound."""
